  "label": "Temple of the Faultlight Canon",
  "description": "Temple of the Faultlight Canon serves as Seamglass Meridian’s principal sanctuary for rites timed to the city’s calibrated twilight bands. Its interior is formed from faceted, dust-slick vitrified tile, with grounded gutters and lensing cisterns drawn inward to create a central basin of shallow reflective water. Mirror-slat clerestories admit the copper-white spectrum as narrow, measurable beams that cross the nave like ruled lines. The sanctuary’s floor follows the fault-limned seam geometry in inlaid glass, fixing devotion to the city’s navigational order and the hushlit lattice beyond.",
